<item>
            <title>[LU-3677] HSM-archived files are no more set DIRTY at eviction</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3677</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the MDT evicts a client, it checks for still opened files, for this client. If one of those files was opened for write, and was archived, from a HSM point of view, we could have missed file modifications. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LOD/OSP changes introduce a regression for this feature.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
